Package utility

Class VariablePositionTableComparator

java.lang.Object
utility.VariablePositionTableComparator
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Comparator<java.lang.String>
public final class VariablePositionTableComparator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<java.lang.String>
Implementation of the java.util.Comparator<java.lang.String> interface to sort String representations of genome positions that may contain "I" characters to represent insertions according to their integer value and number of contained "I"s.

For example the strings "3","5","2","4","4I","4II","4III" are sorted as "2","3","4","4I","4II","4III","5" and would represent an insertion of length three at position 4.

Version:
2.0
Author:
Alexander Seitz, Simon Hackl
